    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-06T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-06T03:34:00-05:00" n="554"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-06T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 7—5:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 1, 6 p.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d554fn10">Not printed; it contained
                        summary of note no. 481, June 21, from the British Ambassador, <ref
                            target="#pg_587">p. 587</ref>, with instructions to “Cable your comment
                        to Department, Tokyo and Peking.” (File no. 861.77/2137.)</note> Statement
                    that the Russian manager approached Japanese banks probably not true. Technical
                    Board will take the stand manager has no right to negotiate loan without the
                    consent of Board. Statement South Manchuria Railway has advanced coal true.
                    Chinese Eastern at the present time owes South <pb facs="0715" n="591"
                        xml:id="pg_591"/> Manchuria 2,000,000 yen but the latter repeatedly declares
                    no hurry for payment … By reason of failure of Allies to pay military
                    transportation railway urgently needs $10,000,000 to pay debts, provide safe
                    working capital, and for contingencies. Therefore, I approve Japanese suggestion
                    of Allies loan but only to be expended Technical Board control. If such loan not
                    made am certain big bond issue taels will be made. Have cabled Tokyo, Peking but
                    advise the Department that I have no safe code either place. Did the Department
                    receive my cipher telegram June 23 from Tokyo?<note n="11" xml:id="d554fn11"
                        >Apparently refers to no. 215, June 24, 11 a.m., <ref target="#pg_588">p.
                            588</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
